          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[120] It is, however, an interesting illustration of how an O.T. writer (like so many of the prophets), while forbidding strenuously the representation of the Deity in any material form, does not hesitate to use anthropomorphisms in describing His appearances to men. Ch. ",
        "children": []
